), 
<date id="FFA81058112BFFF2F274FCFDA4D1035C" box="[1284,1432,848,874]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" value="1978-07-01">
<number id="3DDE24BF112BFFF2F274FCFDA45D035C" box="[1284,1300,848,874]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" value="1.0">1</number>
. VII. 
<number id="3DDE24BF112BFFF2F22AFCFDA4D1035C" box="[1370,1432,848,874]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" value="1978.0">1978</number>
</date>
, Fasheng Li.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30C6513112BFFF2F7B5FC30A3600381" box="[197,553,925,951]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BA93698112BFFF2F7B5FC30A3600381" blockId="10.[151,1437,152,1183]" box="[197,553,925,951]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B962EA8A112BFFF2F7B5FC30A02C0381" bold="true" box="[197,357,925,951]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F3017608112BFFF2F61CFC30A0FB0381" box="[364,434,925,951]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">China</collectingCountry>
(Xizang).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30C6513112BFFF2F7B5FC6EA00D0432" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA93698112BFFF2F7B5FC6EA00D0432" blockId="10.[151,1437,152,1183]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B962EA8A112BFFF2F7B5FC6EA01803EB" bold="true" box="[197,337,963,989]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet derives from the Latin “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D1B112BFFF2F428FC69A2E503E8" box="[856,940,964,990]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusa">obtusa</taxonomicName>
”; referring to obtuse tip of the distiphallus in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30C6513112BFFF2F7B5FBBDA04604A9" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA93698112BFFF2F7B5FBBDA04604A9" blockId="10.[151,1437,152,1183]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B962EA8A112BFFF2F7B5FBBDA009041C" bold="true" box="[197,320,1040,1066]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D1B112BFFF2F5DEFBBCA2EC041D" authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" box="[686,933,1041,1067]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis id="B962EA8A112BFFF2F5DEFBBCA262041C" box="[686,811,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">V. fasciata</emphasis>
(Meigen)
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be separated from the latter by tergites 
<number id="3DDE24BF112BFFF2F78AFB95A06E0464" box="[250,295,1080,1106]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
with yellowish recumbent scales on anterior half, but scales on tergite 
<number id="3DDE24BF112BFFF2F3EBFB95A5E30464" box="[1179,1194,1080,1106]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" value="3.0">3</number>
less. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D1B112BFFF2F264FB95A4DD0467" box="[1300,1428,1080,1105]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis id="B962EA8A112BFFF2F264FB95A4DD0467" box="[1300,1428,1080,1105]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">V. fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tergites 
<number id="3DDE24BF112BFFF2F787FBF3A04F044E" box="[247,262,1118,1144]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number id="3DDE24BF112BFFF2F632FBF3A018044E" box="[322,337,1118,1144]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" value="3.0">3</number>
have yellowish recumbent scales antero-laterally, tergite 
<number id="3DDE24BF112BFFF2F379FBF3A551044E" box="[1033,1048,1118,1144]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" value="4.0">4</number>
has yellowish recumbent scales anteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
